  • Classes in cu.edu.cujae.graphy.core used by cu.edu.cujae.graphy.algorithms 
    Class Description
    Graph
    The Graph interface represents a graph as an abstract data structure.The graph does not make a distinction with the data type it holds, it just presents an abstract model of a graph.
    Tree
    A tree is a data structure represented by a directed acyclic graph, imitating the shape of a tree.It is a set of connected nodes.
    WeightedGraph
    A weighted graph is a Graph in which each branch is given a numerical weight.A weighted graph is therefore a special type of labeled graph.
  • Classes in cu.edu.cujae.graphy.core used by cu.edu.cujae.graphy.core 
    Class Description
    Edge
    An edge is an ordered pair of the form (u, v).
    EdgeFactory
    This interface defines factories for Edge.
    Graph
    The Graph interface represents a graph as an abstract data structure.The graph does not make a distinction with the data type it holds, it just presents an abstract model of a graph.
    GraphBuilder
    This is an implementation of the builder pattern for constructing graphs.
    Node
    This interface represents nodes or vertices in a graph.
    TreeNode
    An interface representing nodes of a tree.
    Weight
    This interface is used to represents weights in a graph.It is mostly a wrapper over the Comparable interface.
